<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,256,1010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[237,301,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[289,301,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) yellow, with two small dark brown spots, whitish towards eyes. Coronal suture short, about 
<number box="[1326,1336,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1345,1360,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
vertex middle length, a brownish patch on midline at apex of vertex. Pronotum anterior region and lateral regions yellow or brownish yellow, with irregular dark brown or black patterns; central part and posterior region from brownish to dark brownish. Face (
<figureCitation box="[330,395,360,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[381,395,360,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) frontoclypeus brownish, with areas of yellowish or whitish. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1243,360,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1230,1243,360,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) semitransparent, brownish white; clavus and adjacent areas darker. 
<collectingCountry box="[687,740,394,417]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing submarginal vein not extended to wing apex (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1359,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1343,1359,394,417]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,256,1010]" box="[198,857,429,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Abdominal apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[446,510,429,452]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[496,510,429,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) large, extending to 
<number box="[730,743,429,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="4.0">4</number>
th sternite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,256,1010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[198,357,464,487]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation box="[530,596,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[582,596,464,487]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad, with small group of microsetae at ventro-cephalic angle of lobe and others scattered near caudal margin. Dorsal appendage (
<figureCitation box="[765,830,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[816,830,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) immovably fused to margin, curved ventrally, slightly branched at apex, not extended beyond pygofer apex. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[908,971,533,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[957,971,533,556]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongated, acutely narrowing at apex, with 
<number box="[151,165,568,591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="3.0">3</number>
macrosetae not far from terminal part. Setosity near base absent. Style slim, apex sharp; preapical lobe small, cheliform. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[389,502,602,625]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Figs. 
<number box="[449,502,602,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="9.11">9, 11</number>
</figureCitation>
) articulated to connective. Aedeagal shaft slightly curved dorsally in lateral view, with pair of small branched processes near base. Gonopore apical, on ventral surface. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1253,637,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 11" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1846,1867]" captionTargetBox="[184,1384,187,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,146,1853]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 11. Rufitidia forficata sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Forewing. 4. Hind wing. 5. Abdominal apodemes. 6. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 7. Subgenital plate. 8. Style. 9. Aedeagus, ventral view. 10. Aedeagus, lateral view. 11. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275405/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1226,1253,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped, arms long, central lobe absent, stem short and inflated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,256,1010]" box="[198,375,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[198,272,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">Length</emphasis>
: 3.3 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
